<topic id="dita-apply-profiling-conditional-set">
  <title>Applying Profiling Condition Sets in DITA</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>DITA<indexterm>Profiling<indexterm>Applying profiling condition
            sets</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>All defined <xref href="dita-condition-sets-management.dita#dita-condition-sets-management"
        >Profiling Condition Sets</xref> are available as shortcuts in the <xref
        href="../topics/profiling-conditional-text-menu.dita#profiling-conditional-text-menu"
        format="dita"><uicontrol><image href="../img/ProfilingToolbar16.png" id="image_v2c_s4f_wr"
          />Profiling / Conditional Text</uicontrol> toolbar menu</xref>. Select a menu entry to
      apply the condition set. The filtered content is then grayed-out in the
        <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode, <xref
        href="outliner-view.dita#outliner-view"><uicontrol>Outline</uicontrol>
        view</xref>, and <xref href="dita-maps-manager.dita#dita-maps-manager"><uicontrol>DITA Maps
          Manager</uicontrol> view</xref>. Your selection will also be used as the <xref
        href="publish-profiled-text.dita#publish-profiled-text">default condition set</xref> in
      transformation scenarios (this can be changed in the <uicontrol>Filters</uicontrol> tab). An
      element is filtered-out when one of its attributes is part of the condition set and its value
      does not match any of the values covered by the condition set.</p>
